      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The 2011 Libya intervention was a classic example of a \"regime change\" operation that prioritized regime removal over post-conflict planning. The US and its allies were so focused on achieving a quick victory that they neglected to establish a viable, inclusive government, paving the way for the chaos that followed. In hindsight, the intervention's humanitarian success was a Pyrrhic victory, as the long-term consequences of the power vacuum and regional instability far outweighed the initial benefits.",
